  "body": "When trying to impersonate an account with Link tokens either on Arbitrum or Rinkeby Arbitrum no transactions can be sent with that impersonated account because the following error returns:\r\n\r\n'(node:36286) UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: ProviderError: sender doesn't have enough funds to send tx. The max upfront cost is: 68185536000000000 and the sender's account only has: 0'\r\n\r\nEven though I know the user I'm impersonating has both ETH and Link to support what I need to do (as you can check in https://testnet.arbiscan.io/address/0x2c6d750d5a9193ad079885ecb6efc9c591bfc687 this is a valid whale address with ETH and Link holdings)\r\n\r\nThe code below is the function being used to impersonate and access an account's funds:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst hardhat = require('hardhat');\r\n\r\nconst linkAddressArbitrumRinkeby = '0x615fBe6372676474d9e6933d310469c9b68e9726;\r\nconst erc20Factory = await ethers.getContractFactory('ERC20');\r\nconst token = (await erc20Factory.attach(linkAddressArbitrumRinkeby)) as ERC20;\r\n\r\nconst whale = '0x2C6D750d5a9193ad079885ECB6efC9c591bfc687' \r\n\r\nconst getTokenForAccount = async (token: ERC20, amountConverted: string, user: string, whale: string) => {\r\n    // ETH whale\r\n    await hardhat.network.provider.request({\r\n      method: 'hardhat_impersonateAccount',\r\n      params: [whale],\r\n    });\r\n    const whaleSigner = await hardhat.ethers.provider.getSigner(whale);\r\n    \r\n    await token.connect(whaleSigner).transfer(user, amountConverted);\r\n    // Stop Impersonating ETH whale\r\n    await hardhat.network.provider.request({\r\n      method: 'hardhat_stopImpersonatingAccount',\r\n      params: [whale],\r\n    });\r\n};\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\neven actions like getting the balance of the whale address stop the hardhat code. For e.g.\r\n```\r\n  const balance = await hardhat.ethers.provider.getBalance(user);\r\n  console.log({ balance });\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis code above does not run (is stuck in the await call)\r\n\r\nWhat could be wrong?\r\n\r\n\r\nUsing https://arb-rinkeby.g.alchemy.com/v2/KEY_HERE as a provider",
